task 3 Terminal Text Editors

nano
- text editor you can use on the commandline 
- ex. nano filename
- all files in linux fundamentals have been made using nano
- use ctrl X to exit and follow the prompts at the bottom above the commands
- features included:
  -- searching for text
  -- copying and pasting
  -- jumping to a line number
  -- finding out what line a number you are on 


VIM
- more advanced editor than nano
- is customisable
- has syntax highlighting
- works on all terminals
 -- nano does not work on every terminal

